Commands for start/stop/restart services using Systemctl in Linux:

Systemctl is a controller or utility of Systemd with auxiliary in manage services, these commands are executed in mode root, if one is not in mode root system, requesting password of root.

-->For starting a service:
sudo systemctl start cronListener

-->For stopping a service:
sudo systemctl stop cronListener

-->For restarting a service:
sudo systemctl restart cronListener
